727720f-b.text:
Queens Boulevard, north side, east from Van Loon Street to Broadway showing in the foreground of both views the former Association Hall (square building). It was originally the Baptist Church, erected in 1809. At that time it was a one story building. Beyond it are peaked roof hoses owned by A Proctor in 1873. At the corner of the above mentioned Boulevard and Broadway is the Higgs Hotel of 1891.
March 1923
View 2: May 1929
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
